<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Kill Jumping and Rotations</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Ardecki -Extinguisher of light-">Ardecki -Extinguisher of light-</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:07 a.m. 13/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Kill Jumping and Rotations<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/the_rathe.cgi?read=166" TARGET=_self>Kill Jumping and Rotations</A> (Daraden Bloodstorm - OSS)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Yo dude,

<P>You did what any other fair player would of done. You should not worrie over something like this. What you do next time is call in a High level wizard from your guild , HEHEHEH Then you and the wiz only go after what he goes after.
<P>He will usually leave to another zone..
<P>IT works. I know.. :)
<P>&gt; Tell me if I am wrong. I was hanging out in
<BR>&gt; NRo with a lower level guildmate, watching
<BR>&gt; his back and killing the occsional Thug. I
<BR>&gt; am a level 23 warrior and he
<P>&gt; is a level 15 Cleric. There was another guy
<BR>&gt; by the name of Ansel there, a level 14
<BR>&gt; paladin. He was jumping all over every derv
<BR>&gt; that spawned. I asked him, and
<P>&gt; everyone else there, if we could form an
<BR>&gt; acceptable rotation so that everyone there
<BR>&gt; could get a kill. While everyone else was
<BR>&gt; amenable to a rotation, his
<P>&gt; answer was no. He said he wanted a Free For
<BR>&gt; All. You hit it, you get it. I asked him at
<BR>&gt; least 4 or 5 times to not do that because it
<BR>&gt; creates anarchy and
<P>&gt; chaos. "Nope sorry." was his
<BR>&gt; reply. I said fine. If you want to do that
<BR>&gt; then lets play it like that. I then ran
<BR>&gt; after every derv he ran after. I would get
<BR>&gt; there
<P>&gt; simutltaneously with him. But because I
<BR>&gt; could do so much more damage I would get the
<BR>&gt; kill and he complained I was kill stealing.
<BR>&gt; Was that not "Free For
<P>&gt; All"? First and best gets all the loot?
<BR>&gt; That is what he wanted right? SO then he
<BR>&gt; calls in his friend Merula. Merula conned
<BR>&gt; low blue to me so even though he
<P>&gt; was anon I had no fear of him. I asked him
<BR>&gt; to be fair and ask if everyone wanted a
<BR>&gt; rotation. He refused. What his buddy Ansel
<BR>&gt; said is supposed to go. They
<P>&gt; then proceeded to jump kills and take
<BR>&gt; whatever derv they wanted. Was this fair? Am
<BR>&gt; I to be labeled a KS'er because I went along
<BR>&gt; with his idea of Free For
<P>&gt; All? Tell me because I am unsure. I know
<BR>&gt; eventually my name will get posted by him
<BR>&gt; and I shall be branded a KS'er. I have never
<BR>&gt; KS'ed nor did I intend to.
<P>&gt; Was this KS'ing? IF we both run to the same
<BR>&gt; mob and hit it at the same time, who's kill
<BR>&gt; is it? That is exactly why I suggested
<BR>&gt; rotating, as it prevents
<P>&gt; situations like that. SOmeone tell me what's
<BR>&gt; right. E-mail me at anson357@earthlink.net.
<BR>&gt; Post it on my guilds message board at
<BR>&gt; www.tmerlo.com/eq or just
<P>&gt; reply here. Either way, let me know what is
<BR>&gt; right.
<P>&gt; Daraden Bloodstorm
<P>&gt; Level 23 Warrior
<P>&gt; Order of the Shifting Sands
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
